<vulnerability_guide>
  <title>CBC BIT FLIPPING ATTACKS</title>

  <critical>CBC (Cipher Block Chaining) bit flipping allows attackers to manipulate encrypted data without knowing the key. By flipping bits in a ciphertext block, the corresponding bits in the next block's plaintext are flipped predictably. This enables bypassing authentication, modifying encrypted cookies, and manipulating encrypted data fields.</critical>

  <scope>
    - CBC mode vulnerability exploitation
    - Encrypted cookie manipulation
    - Authentication bypass via bit flipping
    - Predictable IV attacks
    - Padding oracle interaction
    - Encrypted parameter tampering
  </scope>

